<docs>
	<doc for="HeaderHandler">
		<summary>
			<para>Represents the method that will handle processing of headers on the stream
      during deserialization.</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="headers">The headers of the event. </param>
		<remarks>
			<para><see cref="System.Runtime.Remoting.Messaging.Header"/> objects are used to convey 
   information about a remote function call (for example, transaction ID or a
   method signature).</para>
			<para>When you create a <see cref="System.Runtime.Remoting.Messaging.HeaderHandler"/>, you identify the method that
will handle the event. For an overview, see <see topic="cpconeventsdelegates"/>. </para>
		</remarks>
		<seealso topic="cpconeventsdelegates"/>
	</doc></docs>
